    • Method Detail

      • compareExcelFiles

        public void compareExcelFiles​(java.lang.String file1,
                              java.lang.String file2,
                              java.lang.String sheet1,
                              java.lang.String sheet2,
                              java.lang.String resultFilePath)
                       throws java.io.IOException
        This Function will compare two Excel files and show if the are the same or not. created to compare expected values in excel sheet by the one exported from MS dynamcs. It will works only on excel with extension .xlsx (2007-365 extension)
        Parameters:
        file1 - Path to the first Excel file
        file2 - Path to the second Excel file.
        sheet1 - Name of sheet in first Excel sheet you want to compare.
        sheet2 - Name of sheet in second Excel sheet you want to compare.
        resultFile - Path to .doc field you will write in.
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - -used to handle FileNotFoundException and InvalidPathException
